---
description: Keep Rust code warning-free; do not introduce compiler or Clippy warnings
globs: ["**/*.rs", "**/Cargo.toml"]
alwaysApply: false
---

# Rust: no warnings in committed code

- Do not introduce Rust compiler warnings or Clippy lints. Fix any existing warnings in files you touch when feasible.
- Before finishing Rust changes, run `cargo check --workspace` (and optionally `cargo clippy --workspace`) and resolve any warnings.
- The project uses a pre-commit hook (see docs/TESTING.md) that runs `cargo check --workspace` with `RUSTFLAGS="-D warnings"`; commits will be rejected if warnings remain.
